text: Albert Schippel (1862–1935) was an American architect in the Midwest. He designed buildings including: *Rice County Jail, (1910), Faribault, Minnesota *Oleander Saloon, (1901), Mankato, Wisconsin *Immanuel Lutheran School, (1903), Mankato, Wisconsin *German Evangelical Ladies Seminary, (1910), Mankato, Wisconsin. The seminary has since become Bethany Lutheran College. ==References== ==External links== *Albert Schippel, '20th Century Midwest Architect' Category:1862 births Category:1935 deaths Category:Architects from Wisconsin Category:People from Wisconsin
